definition.value: The hydroxy monocarboxylic acid anion that is the conjugate base of 3-(6-hydroxyindol-3-yl)lactic acid.
A derivative of aniline in which the hydrogen at position 2 has been substituted by fluorine. It is used as a pharmaceutical intermediate
A diadenosyl triphosphate having the two 5'-adenosyl residues attached at the P(1)- and P(2)-positions.
A hydroxy- and oxo- fatty acid comprising hexanoic acid substituted at C-2 and C-4 with oxo and hydroxy groups respectively.
Any L-cysteine derivative obtained by conversion of the thiol group into a sulfide.
Any mannoside in which the anomeric centre has alpha-configuration.
An unsaturated fatty acyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of trans-oct-2-enoic acid.
An indoledione that is the 2,3-diketo derivative of indole.
A medium-chain fatty acyl-CoA having hexanoyl as the S-acyl group.
A 3',5'-cyclic purine nucleotide having hypoxanthine as the nucleobase.
A fatty acid methyl ester resulting from the formal condensation of the carboxy group of oleic acid with methanol.
A dichlorohydroquinone that is hydroquinone substituted by chloro groups at positions 2 and 5 respectively.
A purine 2'-deoxyribonucleoside having O(6)-methylguanine as the nucleobase.
A trihydroxyanthraquinone that is anthracene-9,10-dione substituted by hydroxy groups at positions 1, 2 and 3.
A pyrimidine that is a derivative of cytosine, having a methyl group at the 5-position.
A dihydroxyflavanone that is flavanone substituted by hydroxy groups at positions 5 and 7 and a methoxy group at position 4' (the 2S stereoisomer).
The beta-anomer of alpha-D-glucosyl-(1->3)-D-mannopyranose
A member of the class of prostaglandins C that is prosta-5,11,13-trien-1-oic acid carrying oxo and hydroxy substituents at positions 9 and 15 respectively (the 5Z,13E,15S-stereoisomer).
An  anthracenetriol that is anthracene substituted by hydroxy groups at positions 1, 8 and 9.
A  saturated organic heteromonocyclic parent that is a three-membered heterocycle of two carbon atoms and one oxygen atom.
A member of the class of leukotrienes that is leukotriene B4 in which the terminal methyl group has undergone formal oxidation to the corresponding carboxylic acid.
A 3-methylguanine that is 3,7-dihydro-6H-purin-6-one substituted by an amino group at position 2 and a methyl group at position 3.
An aminobenzoic acid that is salicylic acid substituted by an amino group at position 4.
A trihydroxyflavanone having a structure of naringenin prenylated at C-6.
A polysaccharide composed of repeating units of arabinosylgalactose.
An alpha-amino acid that is propanoic acid bearing an amino substituent at position 2 and a 1H-imidazol-4-yl group at position 3.
A keto-disaccharide that is beta-D-galactosyl-(1->4)-beta-D-glucose in which the hydroxy group at position 3 of the galactosyl moiety has been oxidised to the corresponding ketone.
